<div id="missionsScreen" class="screen">
    <button class="backBtn backToMap">← Back to Map</button>

    <div id="missionCard">
        <div id="missionTitle">Kangaroo Mission</div>
        <div id="missionImg"></div>
        <div class="stars">⭐⭐⭐</div>
        <div id="missionDesc">
            Help the <b>Ranger Team</b> understand how kangaroos are coping
            with changing seasons.
            <br><br>
            <b>Your mission:</b> notice where the kangaroos rest, where they
            feed, and how much shade they have. Kids can log what they see in
            three simple steps:
            <ol>
                <li>Count how many kangaroos you can spot.</li>
                <li>Circle on the map where you saw them resting.</li>
                <li>Pick one “challenge” they might face (heat, drought, cars).</li>
            </ol>
            This turns a normal walk into a mini-field study – easy to run,
            fun for kids, and full of data the zoo can actually use.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="managerPanel">
        <h3>For Zoo Management (Consulting Layer)</h3>
        <p>
            Behind the scenes, this mission feeds a simple data model:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Heat-stress risk zones along the route.</li>
            <li>Visitor attention hotspots (where families actually stop).</li>
            <li>Animal “challenge” tags chosen by visitors.</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top:6px;">
            We use this to build dashboards that show:
        </p>
        <ul>
